description:
&lt;p&gt;The Birmingham &amp; Midland Eye Centre at City/Sandwell Hospital has a vacancy for a staff nurse to work in our busy ophthalmic out patient departments. We are interested in recruiting an enthusiastic, highly motivated and hard working team player with excellent communication skills. The post offers the opportunity to develop various skills such as pre-op assessment, biometrics, and Fluorescein angiography amongst many others. Ophthalmic experience is desirable but not essential as the successful candidate will have the opportunity to develop ophthalmic competencies required for the role. The post holder will need to be flexible and be willing to work across all Trust sites venues/internal rotation to other departments. Late shifts and Saturday working will be part of the rostered shift pattern. Should you require any further information regarding this post please contact BMEC OPD Manager Cindy Sanghera&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
